c c --synthesis (wDNNF share-and-branch) regression: this minimized projected
c c CNF was historically a no-witness failure. Var 5 and 6 are pure-negative
c c outputs; share-mode used to pin one sibling to +6 (rp=FREE -> default +v)
c c while another pinned -6 (rp=2 pure neg), violating wDNNF. The orig_polarity
c c fix forces both pins to -6. We assert the emitted circuit is weak-
c c decomposable (the wDNNF invariant) -- not its count (synthesis mode
c c deliberately produces a wrong count).
c p show 1 2 3 4 0
c c RUN: %solver --compile %t.nnf --synthesis 1 %s
c c RUN: %ddnnf_verify %t.nnf --check-weak-decomposable
p cnf 8 3
-7 -5 -1 0
-7 -6 -1 0
-6 -5 -3 0
